The largest Great Lake is Lake Superior. It is the largest freshwater lake in the world by surface area and volume, with a surface area of 31,700 square miles (82,100 square kilometers) and a volume of 2,900 cubic miles (12,100 cubic kilometers). The lake is shared by the United States and Canada, with the majority of it located in the United States. Lake Superior is also the deepest of the Great Lakes, with a maximum depth of 1,332 feet (406 meters).